	   <tr><td colspan=2>As someone who has a cleric as a main character, let me assure you, there is no class worse to create for the purpose of making money. Clerics require expensive armor AND spells, where most classes require only one or the other. Also, they don't solo easily, and then only in limited types of situations (mainly single static spawns). The only Money maker for clerics is rezzing, and the only rezzes that make much cash are the lvl 44, 49 and 56 rez. I doubt you would want to get your cleric to lvl 44 just to make plat.<br><br>Your best bet, if all you really want is to equip your monk, would be to level your monk up to the point that he can hunt in a zone like east commons. Then kill bears, cats, wolves, spiders and spiderlings. Save all pelts/skins that say low/medium or high quality, and all silks. Find a tailor, and trade tailoring supplies for cured silk armor (or if you are really lucky, Wu's). Now, if you don't want to farm pelts with a monk, since this may encumber him fast, stick to just the silks. they are very light.<br><br>However, if you are dead set on a cleric, there are 2 paths you can take: one is to equip him for ac, which is cheaper, and faster, and will be better for soloing in befallen. In that case, a full set of banded armor will be ideal. get moonstone rings (cheaper than plat jewelry, and mana will do more for you at low levels), and jasper gold earrings. Total for this setup should be about 200pp<br><br>The other approach is wisdom over ac. This is only recommended if you plan to group nearly all the time. Start with the same rings/earrings as above, but add a silver ruby veil, instead of banded mask. (you're already over 200pp now btw). get savant cap, polished bone bracelets, platinum armbands, foreman's tunic (or crystal covered shroud), gatorscale legs, blackened iron medallion, and fill the rest of the slots in with banded. this setup would probably cost you about 500-600pp total, more if you go for the crystal covered shroud. With this setup, your ac will be low, but you can cast more spells. You will really want to be in a group.<br><br>BTW, notice that equipping this cleric will cost you more than a full set of cured silk.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr&nbsp;&nbsp;9 15:53:32 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
